?????

1)  Install Tight VNC
      sudo apt update
      sudo apt install tightvncserver
      
2)  Initialize       
      vncserver
      vncserver -kill :1
      
3)  Startup Config File
      mv ~/.vnc/xstartup ~/.vnc/xstartup.bak
      nano ~/.vnc/xstartup
        #!/bin/bash
        xrdb $HOME/.Xresources
        startxfce4 &
        
4)  Turn it into an executable
      chmod +x ~/.vnc/xstartup
         
5)  Restart Server
      vncserver -localhost
  
To change passwords: 
      vncpasswd
